parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The infotainment screen has spider cracks
the system glitches out
makes random calls
switches to radio stations or Pandora
and the controls do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause injuries, distractions, and accidents.
symptoms: The sunroof glass shatters or explodes
causing glass to fall on the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can cause accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: The backup camera flickers or fails to load completely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the temperature control link can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The temperature control link slips out of place
making it difficult to defrost the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TPMS can cause tire blowouts, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The TPMS malfunctions
causing the system to trigger auto deflation of tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can cause accidents or injuries, especially if it occurs while driving.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air blower control cable can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The cable controlling the air blower from cold to warm will disconnect.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the TCS can cause loss of control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The TCS symbol appears on the dashboard
indicating a malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the tire tread can cause loss of control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The tire tread separates
causing significant body damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the headrests can cause chronic and acute neck, head, and back pain.
symptoms: The headrests jut forward at an extreme angle
causing discomfort and pain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle catching on fire can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire
resulting in significant damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The infotainment system randomly dials phone numbers
changes channels
and selects menu items; the system reboots itself; the backup camera intermittently cuts out; the navigation system shuts down and reboots continuously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor radio reception can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The radio signal fades in and out
making it difficult to listen to the radio.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and hesitation can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or hesitates while driving
often accompanied by warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission issues can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate when shifting gears
often accompanied by warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
causing issues with the push-to-start button
navigation system
and other electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system issues can cause accidents, especially when driving on hills.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls backwards or forwards when parked on a hill
even with the emergency brake engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to address recall issues can cause accidents or other safety hazards.
symptoms: The vehicle has an open recall for the rear camera wiring harness
but no repair parts are available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake caliper can cause the brakes to seize, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Squeaking or grinding noise from the rear brakes
uneven brake pad wear
heat emanating from the rear brakes
and the parking brake failing to engage or disengage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The parking brake handle does not return to its normal position
the parking brake does not engage or disengage
the vehicle rolls or moves when parked on an incline
and the parking brake makes a loud noise when engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes make a loud noise when applied
and the vehicle takes longer than usual to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Seam Corrosion and Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and leakage of the fuel tank seam can cause gasoline to leak onto the road, posing a fire hazard and risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds. Additionally, the hazardous fumes can accumulate in the vehicle's cabin, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline
fuel leaks from the top of the tank
puddling of gas under the car
gas smell when filling the tank past a certain level (e.g.
gas smell when parking in a garage
decreased gas mileage.
